-- PDVSA Boat Sinks in Venezuela, One Missing, Globovision Says
-- B y   C h a r l i e   D e v e r e u x
-- 2012-01-12T22:27:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/pdvsa-boat-sinks-in-venezuela-one-missing-globovision-says.html
A boat carrying nine workers from
state oil company Petroleos de  Venezuela  sank in Lake Maracaibo
in the northwest of Venezuela,  Globovision reported , citing
Jolbis Bermudez, second commander of the firemen’s unit.  One person is missing after the remaining eight were
rescued, the Caracas-based television network cited Bermudez as
saying.  A PDVSA spokesman, who requested anonymity in line with
company policy, said he couldn’t confirm the accident.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Charlie Devereux in Caracas at 
 cdevereux3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  